HEADWORD: Hopscotch
<hw>Hop"scotch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A child's game, in
which a player, hopping on one foot, drives a stone from one compartment
to another of a figure traced or scotched on the ground; -- called also
<altname>hoppers</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

